# Auto-resolve CHANGELOG conflicts by keeping BOTH sides (git's built-in `union`
# merge driver). Many independent PRs append entries to CHANGELOG.md's
# [Unreleased] section at the same spot, so without this every merge conflicts
# every other open PR on this one file. `union` concatenates both sides' hunks
# instead of raising a conflict — order within [Unreleased] is cosmetic and the
# /changelogs parser keys on `### ` headings, so this is safe.
CHANGELOG.md merge=union
